## Installation

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/<your-org>/CAGE.git
cd CAGE

# Create and activate the Conda environment
conda env create -f environment.yml
conda activate cage

# Install in editable mode
pip install -e .

# Verify the installation
python -c "import cage; print(cage.__version__)"
```

---

## Input Data

The pipeline expects three TCGA ESCA files in the input directory
(configurable via `--input-dir`):

| File | Description | Dimensions |
|------|-------------|------------|
| `TCGA_ESCA_STAR_Counts.csv` | Raw STAR gene-level counts | genes × 197 samples |
| `ESCA_vst_normalized_matrix.csv` | DESeq2 variance-stabilised expression | genes × 197 samples |
| `TCGA_ESCA_Metadata.csv` | Clinical, demographic, and molecular metadata | 197 samples × 137 covariates |

**Data access**: Raw data are available from the
[GDC Data Portal](https://portal.gdc.cancer.gov/) under project TCGA-ESCA.

---

## Pipeline Architecture

```
┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                              CAGE Pipeline                                   │
├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                                                    │
│  Step 2 ─► Step 3 ─► Step 4 ─► Step 5 ─► Step 6 ─► Step 6b ─► Step 7 ─► Step 8  │
│  Cohort    Baselines  Deep      CDPS     Biological  Top-25    Manuscript External │
│  Curation             Model    Ranking   Validation  Priority  Packaging  Release  │
│  (Phase I)           (Phase II)(Phase III)(Phase IV) (post-6)  (Phase V) (Phase V)│
│                                                                                    │
└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Model Architecture

```
Input (5000 genes)
       │
  ┌────▼────┐
  │ Feature │  L1 / hard-concrete
  │  Gate   │  sparsity regularisation
  └────┬────┘
       │ (gated expression)
  ┌────▼────┐
  │ Encoder │  256 → 96 → 48 (latent)
  │ (ReLU + │  with dropout
  │ Dropout)│
  └────┬────┘
       │
  ┌────┼────────────┬────────────────┐
  │    │            │                │
  ▼    ▼            ▼                ▼
Classifier  Adversary   Invariance   Decoder
(tumor/     (confounder (latent-mean  (optional
 normal)     removal     penalty)    reconstruction)
             via GRL)
```

