## Step-by-Step Execution

Every pipeline module exposes a comprehensive `--help` screen with branded
CAGE output, input/output documentation, and usage examples:

```bash
python -m cage.<module_name> --help
```

---

### Step 2 — Cohort Curation and Preprocessing (Phase I)

**Purpose**: Assemble a leakage-free TCGA ESCA cohort, harmonise barcodes,
filter primary tumour/solid-normal samples, construct confounder and
environment strata, process the expression matrix, and generate
patient-grouped nested cross-validation folds.

**Module**: `cage.step2_build_cohort`

#### Run Command

Three usage modes are supported. Use the one matching your compute budget and manuscript target:

```bash
# FAST / exploratory (top-5000 variable genes; ~1 h)
python -m cage.step2_build_cohort \
  --input-dir . \
  --output-dir outputs/step2_cohort \
  --n-top-variable-genes 5000 \
  --n-outer-folds 5 --n-inner-folds 3 \
  --run-cohort-flow-figure --seed 2026

# BALANCED (top-20000 variable genes; ~4–8 h)
python -m cage.step2_build_cohort \
  --input-dir . \
  --output-dir outputs/step2_cohort \
  --n-top-variable-genes 20000 \
  --n-outer-folds 5 --n-inner-folds 3 \
  --run-cohort-flow-figure --seed 2026

# all_genes mode (all ~39k biologically filtered genes; one flag)
python -m cage.step2_build_cohort \
  --input-dir . \
  --output-dir outputs/step2_cohort \
  --rigor-profile all_genes \
  --n-outer-folds 5 --n-inner-folds 3 \
  --run-cohort-flow-figure --seed 2026
```

`--rigor-profile all_genes` is equivalent to passing `--use-all-filtered-genes
--run-cohort-flow-figure --bootstrap-ci-n 1000 --run-calibration
--run-subgroup-sensitivity --run-perturbation` simultaneously. Individual flags
still override the preset when explicitly supplied.

> **Gene sensitivity analysis (optional post-hoc)**
> ```bash
> python -m cage.step2_gene_sensitivity \
>   --input-dir . --output-dir outputs/step2_sensitivity \
>   --gene-sensitivity-grid 5000 10000 20000 all
> ```
> Produces `gene_cap_sensitivity_metrics.csv` and a Jaccard comparison figure.
> Confirm Jaccard ≥ 0.80 between adjacent caps before claiming top-gene stability.

#### Phase-Specific Options

| Flag | Default | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `--counts-csv` | auto | Override path to `TCGA_ESCA_STAR_Counts.csv` |
| `--vst-csv` | auto | Override path to `ESCA_vst_normalized_matrix.csv` |
| `--metadata-csv` | auto | Override path to `TCGA_ESCA_Metadata.csv` |
| `--min-count` | 10 | Minimum raw count threshold for DE-validation gene filter |
| `--min-samples-per-gene` | 10 | Minimum samples with count ≥ `--min-count` |
| `--near-zero-variance-threshold` | 0.01 | Minimum per-gene variance on the VST matrix |
| `--n-top-variable-genes` | 5000 | Speed-oriented cap on highest-variance genes; NOT a biological requirement |
| `--use-all-filtered-genes` | off | Retain all genes passing dedup + variance filter (no top-N cap) |
| `--gene-sensitivity-grid` | off | Sweep multiple caps (e.g. `5000 10000 20000 all`) |
| `--rigor-profile` | standard | `all_genes` enables all rigorous options in one flag |
| `--n-outer-folds` | 5 | Outer patient-grouped CV folds |
| `--n-inner-folds` | 3 | Inner CV folds for hyperparameter tuning |
| `--environments` | smoking sex histology country stage | Environment strata for invariance |
| `--confounder-columns` | gender, smoking, histology, country, stage | Metadata columns to integer-encode |
| `--run-cohort-flow-figure` | off | Render cohort-flow diagram |
| `--no-zscore` | on | Skip global z-scoring (default; per-fold z-score in Steps 3–4) |

#### Processing Steps

1. **Load** raw counts, VST-normalised expression, and clinical metadata.
2. **Harmonise** full sample barcodes and extract 12-character patient IDs.
3. **Filter** for primary tumour (01) and solid-normal (11) samples only.
4. **Transpose** expression to samples × genes; remove duplicate genes.
5. **Variance filter** near-zero variance genes (removes ~34% of genes).
6. **Select genes**: all filtered genes (`--use-all-filtered-genes`) or top-N by variance.
7. **Encode** categorical confounders (sex, smoking, histology, country, stage).
8. **Assign** environment strata for downstream invariance penalties.
9. **Generate** patient-grouped nested CV fold assignments (no leakage).

#### Outputs

| File | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `master_samples_primary.csv` | Curated patient/sample table with all covariates |
| `normalized_primary_matrix.csv` | VST samples × genes matrix (deep-model input) |
| `counts_primary_matrix.csv` | Filtered raw counts (DE validation input) |
| `grouped_outer_folds.csv` | Patient-safe nested CV fold assignments |
| `confounder_encodings.json` | Integer encoding maps for categorical confounders |
| `phase1_summary.json` | Preprocessing statistics and configuration |
| `preprocessing_gene_filtering_report.csv` | Gene counts at each filtering stage |
| `methods_gene_filtering.txt` | Manuscript-ready Methods paragraph |
| `model_size_report.json` | Estimated model parameters, memory, and training time |
| `gene_cap_sensitivity_metrics.csv` | Jaccard overlap across gene caps (if `--gene-sensitivity-grid`) |
| `figures/` | Cohort flow, sample-type bars, environment strata, gene-filtering funnel |

---

### Step 3 — Grouped Baseline Models

**Purpose**: Train patient-grouped baseline classifiers as reference
benchmarks that the sparse invariant model (Step 4) must exceed.
Produces out-of-fold predictions and per-fold/overall metrics with
bootstrap confidence intervals.

**Module**: `cage.step3_grouped_baselines`

#### Run Command

```bash
python -m cage.step3_grouped_baselines \
  --input-dir outputs/step2_cohort \
  --output-dir outputs/step3_baselines \
  --models logistic elasticnet rf \
  --run-calibration \
  --run-subgroup-sensitivity \
  --bootstrap-ci-n 500 \
  --seed 2026
```

#### Phase-Specific Options

| Flag | Default | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `--step2-dir` | `--input-dir` | Override location of Step 2 outputs |
| `--models` | logistic elasticnet rf | Baseline classifiers to fit (`logistic`, `elasticnet`, `rf`, `decision_tree`) |
| `--decision-threshold` | 0.5 | Probability threshold for binary predictions |
| `--top-n-importances` | 50 | Top-N genes per model in feature-importance table |
| `--bootstrap-ci-n` | 500 | Bootstrap resamples for confidence intervals |
| `--calibration-bins` | 10 | Reliability-diagram bin count |
| `--calibration-strategy` | uniform | Calibration binning strategy (`uniform` or `quantile`) |
| `--environments` | smoking sex histology country stage | Subgroup strata for sensitivity |
| `--run-calibration` | off | Compute and plot probability calibration |
| `--run-subgroup-sensitivity` | off | Report per-environment subgroup metrics |

#### Baseline Models (Pure NumPy)

| Model | Algorithm |
|-------|-----------|
| **Logistic Ridge** | Adam gradient descent with L2 penalty |
| **Elastic-Net Logistic** | FISTA proximal gradient with L1 + L2 |
| **Random Forest** | Bagged weighted-Gini decision trees |
| **Decision Tree** | Single weighted-Gini tree (optional) |

#### Outputs

| File | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `baseline_oof_predictions.csv` | Per-sample OOF probabilities for each model |
| `baseline_train_predictions.csv` | Train-fold probabilities for diagnostic train ROC curves |
| `baseline_per_fold_metrics.csv` | Per-model, per-fold AUROC/AUPRC/BAC/Brier |
| `baseline_summary_metrics.csv` | Overall-OOF and mean-of-folds with 95% CIs |
| `baseline_feature_importance.csv` | Top genes per model (rank, importance score) |
| `baseline_subgroup_metrics.csv` | Per-environment metrics (if enabled) |
| `baseline_calibration.csv` | Reliability diagram data (if enabled) |
| `phase3_summary.json` | Configuration, metrics, and figure manifest |
| `figures/` | ROC curves, PR curves, calibration plot, model-comparison bar chart |

---

### Step 4 — Sparse Invariant Deep Model (Phase II)

**Purpose**: Train the Sparse Invariant Adversarial Autoencoder-Classifier —
the core model combining a learnable per-gene gate, a disease-classification
head, an adversarial confounder module, an optional reconstruction decoder,
and an invariance regulariser over environment strata.

**Module**: `cage.step4_sparse_invariant_model`

#### Recommended Regularized Generalization Run Command

```bash
python -m cage.step4_sparse_invariant_model \
  --input-dir outputs/step2_cohort \
  --output-dir outputs/step4_deep_model \
  --overwrite \
  --latent-dim 32 \
  --hidden-dims 128 64 \
  --sparsity-type l1 \
  --dropout 0.25 \
  --use-decoder \
  --n-epochs 100 \
  --batch-size 64 \
  --lr 8e-4 \
  --weight-decay 5e-4 \
  --patience 20 \
  --sparsity-lambda 0.01 \
  --adv-lambda 0.05 \
  --invariance-lambda 0.001 \
  --recon-lambda 0.15 \
  --adv-ramp-epochs 15 \
  --confounder-column env_histology \
  --environment-column env_sex \
  --run-calibration \
  --run-subgroup-sensitivity \
  --seed 2026
```

#### Architecture Options

| Flag | Default | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `--latent-dim` | 48 | Latent bottleneck dimension |
| `--hidden-dims` | 256 96 | Encoder hidden layer sizes (outer to inner) |
| `--sparsity-type` | l1 | Gate regularisation type (`l1` or `hard-concrete`) |
| `--dropout` | 0.1 | Dropout probability in encoder hidden layers |
| `--use-decoder` / `--no-decoder` | on | Enable/disable reconstruction decoder |

#### Training Options

| Flag | Default | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `--n-epochs` | 150 | Maximum training epochs per fold |
| `--batch-size` | 64 | Mini-batch size |
| `--lr` | 1e-3 | AdamW learning rate |
| `--weight-decay` | 1e-4 | AdamW weight decay |
| `--patience` | 15 | Early-stopping patience (validation AUROC) |
| `--adv-ramp-epochs` | 5 | Linearly ramp adversarial weight from 0 over N epochs |
| `--grad-clip-norm` | 5.0 | Global L2 gradient-norm clip per batch (≤ 0 disables) |

#### Loss Weight Options

| Flag | Default | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `--sparsity-lambda` | 1e-3 | Sparsity penalty weight |
| `--adv-lambda` | 0.5 | Adversarial confounder loss weight |
| `--invariance-lambda` | 0.1 | Environment invariance penalty weight |
| `--recon-lambda` | 0.1 | Reconstruction loss weight |

#### Additional Options

| Flag | Default | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `--confounder-column` | env_histology | Adversary target column |
| `--environment-column` | env_sex | Invariance penalty strata column |
| `--environments` | smoking sex histology country stage | Subgroup columns |
| `--decision-threshold` | 0.5 | Binary prediction threshold |
| `--bootstrap-ci-n` | 500 | Bootstrap resamples for CIs |
| `--run-calibration` | off | Compute probability calibration |
| `--run-subgroup-sensitivity` | off | Report per-environment metrics |
| `--save-latent-embeddings` | on | Save per-sample latent coordinates |
| `--attribution-sample-cap-per-class` | 100 | Cap samples/class for attribution |

#### Composite Loss Function

$$\mathcal{L} = \mathcal{L}_{\text{clf}} + \lambda_s \|\mathbf{g}\|_1 + \lambda_a \mathcal{L}_{\text{adv}} + \lambda_i \frac{1}{K}\sum_{k=1}^{K}\|\boldsymbol{\mu}_k - \boldsymbol{\mu}\|^2 + \lambda_r \mathcal{L}_{\text{recon}}$$

where $\mathbf{g}$ is the gate vector, $\boldsymbol{\mu}_k$ is the
per-environment latent mean, and the adversarial loss gradient is reversed
via a gradient reversal layer.

#### Outputs

| File | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `deep_oof_predictions.csv` | Per-sample tumour probability (OOF, all folds) |
| `deep_train_predictions.csv` | Train-fold tumour probabilities for diagnostic train ROC curves |
| `gate_weights.csv` | Learned sparse gate weights per gene/fold |
| `latent_embeddings.csv` | Per-sample latent vectors |
| `deep_per_fold_metrics.csv` | Per-fold AUROC/AUPRC/BAC/Brier |
| `deep_summary_metrics.csv` | Overall-OOF and mean-of-folds with 95% CIs |
| `deep_subgroup_metrics.csv` | Per-environment subgroup metrics (if enabled) |
| `deep_calibration.csv` | Reliability diagram data (if enabled) |
| `deep_training_history.csv` | Per-fold, per-epoch training/validation loss |
| `checkpoints/` | Trained model weights per fold (`.npz`) |
| `phase2_summary.json` | Configuration, metrics, and figure manifest |
| `figures/` | Latent PCA, gate-weight distributions, ROC/PR curves |

---

### Step 5 — CDPS Ranking (Phase III)

**Purpose**: Integrate deep-model signals into the **Candidate Driver
Priority Score (CDPS)** — a composite ranking that captures attribution
strength, gate selection, cross-fold stability, environment invariance,
and in-silico perturbation sensitivity.

**Module**: `cage.step5_cdps_ranking`

#### Run Command

```bash
python -m cage.step5_cdps_ranking \
  --step2-dir outputs/step2_cohort \
  --step4-dir outputs/step4_deep_model \
  --output-dir outputs/step5_cdps \
  --attribution-method integrated-gradients \
  --ig-steps 50 \
  --stability-top-frac 0.05 \
  --w-attribution 0.30 --w-gate 0.20 --w-stability 0.20 \
  --w-invariance 0.15 --w-perturbation 0.15 \
  --top-ks 25 \
  --run-perturbation \
  --seed 2026
```

#### CDPS Component Weights

$$\text{CDPS} = 0.30 \times \text{attribution} + 0.20 \times \text{gate} + 0.20 \times \text{stability} + 0.15 \times \text{invariance} + 0.15 \times \text{perturbation}$$

| Flag | Default | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `--w-attribution` | 0.30 | Attribution score weight |
| `--w-gate` | 0.20 | Gate weight magnitude |
| `--w-stability` | 0.20 | Cross-fold selection frequency |
| `--w-invariance` | 0.15 | Cross-environment consistency |
| `--w-perturbation` | 0.15 | In-silico perturbation sensitivity |

#### Attribution Options

| Flag | Default | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `--attribution-method` | integrated-gradients | Attribution algorithm (`integrated-gradients`, `grad-x-input`, `gate-weight`) |
| `--attribution-sample-cap-per-class` | 100 | Cap samples/class for attribution computation |
| `--ig-steps` | 50 | Trapezoidal steps for Integrated Gradients |
| `--stability-top-frac` | 0.05 | Top fraction of genes counted per fold for stability |
| `--normalization` | minmax | Per-component normalization (`minmax` or `rank`) |

#### Perturbation Options

| Flag | Default | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `--run-perturbation` | on | Enable tumour ↔ normal expression perturbation |
| `--no-perturbation` | — | Skip perturbation; zero the perturbation component |

#### Outputs

| File | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `ranked_genes_cdps.csv` | Full genome-wide CDPS ranking |
| `top25_genes_cdps.csv` | Top 25 CDPS genes (main-text table) |
| `top100_genes_cdps.csv` | Top 100 CDPS genes (supplementary) |
| `gene_attribution_scores.csv` | Attribution component per gene |
| `gene_stability_scores.csv` | Stability component per gene |
| `gene_invariance_scores.csv` | Invariance component per gene |
| `gene_perturbation_scores.csv` | Perturbation component per gene |
| `figures/` | Stability heatmap, attribution vs perturbation scatter, CDPS barplots |

---

### Step 6 — Biological Validation (Phase IV)

**Purpose**: Validate CDPS-ranked genes through orthogonal biological and
statistical evidence: differential expression, pathway enrichment, PPI
network support, clinicopathologic association, survival analysis, and
subgroup robustness. Produces a final weighted validation-augmented ranking.

**Module**: `cage.step6_biological_validation`

#### Run Command

```bash
python -m cage.step6_biological_validation \
  --step2-dir outputs/step2_cohort \
  --step5-dir outputs/step5_cdps \
  --output-dir outputs/step6_validation \
  --run-enrichment \
  --run-network \
  --run-survival \
  --run-subgroup-sensitivity \
  --gmt-hallmark  data/h.all.v2026.1.Hs.symbols.gmt \
  --gmt-reactome  data/c2.cp.reactome.v2026.1.Hs.symbols.gmt \
  --gmt-kegg-go   data/c2.cp.kegg_medicus.v2026.1.Hs.symbols.gmt \
  --gmt-immune    data/c7.immunesigdb.v2026.1.Hs.symbols.gmt \
  --ppi-edge-list data/ppi_edges.tsv \
  --fdr-threshold 0.05 \
  --lfc-threshold 1.0 \
  --seed 2026
```

#### Differential Expression Options

| Flag | Default | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `--de-method` | welch | DE test method (`welch`, `ranksum`, `nb`) |
| `--fdr-threshold` | 0.05 | Benjamini–Hochberg FDR threshold |
| `--lfc-threshold` | 1.0 | Absolute log₂ fold-change threshold |
| `--min-count` | 10 | Minimum count for DE gene filter |
| `--min-samples-per-gene` | 10 | Minimum samples at `--min-count` |

#### Optional Analyses

| Flag | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `--run-enrichment` | Hallmark / Reactome / KEGG-GO / ImmuneSigDB enrichment on top genes |
| `--run-network` | PPI network-level support (requires `--ppi-edge-list`) |
| `--run-survival` | Univariate survival analysis on tumour cohort |
| `--run-subgroup-sensitivity` | Per-environment tumour-vs-normal consistency |

#### Enrichment Inputs

| Flag | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `--gmt-hallmark` | MSigDB Hallmark `.gmt` file |
| `--gmt-reactome` | Reactome `.gmt` file |
| `--gmt-kegg-go` | KEGG Medicus `.gmt` file |
| `--gmt-immune` | MSigDB C7 ImmuneSigDB `.gmt` file (immunologic signatures) |
| `--top-k-for-enrichment` | Top-K CDPS genes for enrichment foreground (default: 25) |
| `--top-k-for-clinical` | Top-K CDPS genes for clinical/survival (default: 25) |

#### Final Validation Score Weights

$$\text{Validation} = 0.35 \times \text{DE} + 0.20 \times \text{enrichment} + 0.15 \times \text{network} + 0.15 \times \text{clinical} + 0.10 \times \text{subgroup} + 0.05 \times \text{external}$$

| Flag | Default | Component |
|------|---------|-----------|
| `--w-de` | 0.35 | Differential expression |
| `--w-enrichment` | 0.20 | Pathway enrichment |
| `--w-network` | 0.15 | PPI network support |
| `--w-clinical` | 0.15 | Clinical association |
| `--w-subgroup` | 0.10 | Subgroup robustness |
| `--w-external` | 0.05 | External validation |

#### Outputs

| File | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `differential_expression_results.csv` | Gene-wise DE statistics (mean, lfc, p, FDR) |
| `differential_expression_top_hits.csv` | DE filtered by FDR and effect-size |
| `top_cdps_de_support.csv` | CDPS × DE merge for top genes |
| `enrichment_results_hallmark.csv` | Hallmark enrichment results |
| `enrichment_results_reactome.csv` | Reactome enrichment results |
| `enrichment_results_kegg_go.csv` | KEGG/GO enrichment results |
| `enrichment_summary_top_pathways.csv` | Top pathways across all sources |
| `top_gene_pathway_membership.csv` | Gene → pathway membership |
| `network_gene_support.csv` | PPI degree, centrality, component membership |
| `network_edges_top_genes.csv` | Induced subnetwork edges |
| `clinical_association_results.csv` | Stage, histology, residual-disease association |
| `survival_gene_summary.csv` | Log-rank survival analysis per gene |
| `subgroup_sensitivity_summary.csv` | Per-environment robustness |
| `final_validated_gene_ranking.csv` | Integrated ranking (CDPS + validation) |
| `phase4_summary.json` | Configuration and component overview |
| `figures/` | Volcano, CDPS vs lfc scatter, enrichment dot plot, network subgraph, clinical bars |

---

### Step 6b — Top-25 Final Evidence Prioritization (Post-Analysis)

**Purpose**: Takes the top-25 CDPS genes and produces an integrated,
evidence-weighted priority ranking by combining six independent evidence
streams: CDPS/model scores, external replication concordance, differential
expression, clinico-pathologic and survival association, pathway/network
support, and subgroup robustness. Genes are assigned to evidence tiers
(Tier 1 / 2 / 3) and a manuscript-ready table is produced alongside eight
publication-grade figures.

**Module**: `cage.step6b_top25_final_prioritization`

**Position in pipeline**: Optional post-analysis step run after Step 6
(and ideally after Step 8 so external concordance rates are available).
Step 6b outputs are not required by Step 7 but can be copied into the
final manuscript package manually.

#### Run Command

```bash
python -m cage.step6b_top25_final_prioritization \
  --step5-dir outputs/step5_cdps \
  --step6-dir outputs/step6_validation \
  --external-dir outputs/step8_geo_validation \
  --agilent-dir outputs/step8_agilent_validation \
  --output-dir outputs/step6b_top25_prioritization \
  --top-k 25 --seed 2026 \
  --figure-format svg --extra-figure-format pdf \
  --font-family "Times New Roman" --font-size 10 --palette nature \
  --w-cdps 0.30 --w-external 0.20 --w-de 0.15 \
  --w-clinical-survival 0.15 --w-pathway-network 0.10 --w-subgroup 0.10 \
  --tier1-threshold 0.75 --tier2-threshold 0.50
```

All `--external-dir` and `--agilent-dir` inputs are optional. When omitted,
the external replication component is marked as missing and the remaining
weights are proportionally re-normalised per gene.

#### Evidence Scoring

Six components are min-max normalised to [0, 1] and combined as a weighted
sum. When a component is missing for a gene its weight is redistributed
proportionally across the available components so every gene's final score
sums to a comparable [0, 1] scale.

$$\text{Priority} = \sum_{c \in \text{available}} \frac{w_c}{\sum_{c'} w_{c'}} \cdot \text{norm}(s_c)$$

| Flag | Default | Evidence Component |
|------|---------|-------------------|
| `--w-cdps` | 0.30 | CDPS / model score (attribution, gate, stability, invariance, perturbation) |
| `--w-external` | 0.20 | External replication concordance rate across GEO / Agilent cohorts |
| `--w-de` | 0.15 | Absolute effect size (tumor vs normal differential expression) |
| `--w-clinical-survival` | 0.15 | Clinico-pathologic association score or 1 − log-rank p-value |
| `--w-pathway-network` | 0.10 | Pathway membership count and PPI network centrality |
| `--w-subgroup` | 0.10 | Subgroup direction agreement fraction across environment strata |

#### Tier Classification

| Tier | Criterion |
|------|-----------|
| **Tier 1** | `final_priority_score` ≥ `--tier1-threshold` (default 0.75) AND evidence available from ≥ 3 independent components |
| **Tier 2** | `final_priority_score` ≥ `--tier2-threshold` (default 0.50) |
| **Tier 3** | `final_priority_score` < `--tier2-threshold`, or score unavailable |

#### Phase-Specific Options

| Flag | Default | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `--step5-dir` | `outputs/step5_cdps` | Step 5 CDPS output directory |
| `--step6-dir` | `outputs/step6_validation` | Step 6 validation output directory |
| `--external-dir` | — | Step 8 GEO validation outputs (optional) |
| `--agilent-dir` | — | Step 8 Agilent validation outputs (optional) |
| `--top-k` | 25 | Number of top CDPS genes to prioritize |
| `--tier1-threshold` | 0.75 | Score threshold for Tier 1 |
| `--tier2-threshold` | 0.50 | Score threshold for Tier 2 |

#### Outputs

```
outputs/step6b_top25_prioritization/
├── tables/
│   ├── top25_integrated_evidence.csv     # all evidence columns per gene
│   ├── top25_final_priority_ranking.csv  # ranked by final_priority_score
│   ├── top25_tier_summary.csv            # tier counts, gene lists, mean scores
│   ├── top25_missing_evidence_report.csv # per-gene missing component flags
│   └── top25_manuscript_table.csv        # clean manuscript-ready table
├── figures/
│   ├── top25_final_score_waterfall.svg
│   ├── top25_evidence_component_heatmap.svg
│   ├── top25_tiered_ranking_barplot.svg
│   ├── top25_external_concordance_heatmap.svg
│   ├── top25_de_vs_cdps_scatter.svg
│   ├── top25_clinical_survival_summary.svg
│   ├── top25_network_pathway_support.svg
│   └── top25_missing_evidence_map.svg
├── reports/
│   ├── top25_prioritization_summary.md   # tier distribution + score summary
│   ├── top25_methods_text.md             # Methods section draft
│   └── top25_results_text.md             # Results section draft with ranked table
├── manifests/
│   ├── input_file_manifest.csv
│   ├── output_manifest.csv
│   ├── figure_manifest.csv
│   ├── scoring_config.json               # weights, thresholds, normalization method
│   └── reproducibility.json             # timestamp, seed, script SHA-256, NumPy version
└── logs/
    └── step6b_top25_final_prioritization.log
```

#### Integrated Evidence Columns (in `top25_integrated_evidence.csv`)

`gene` · `original_cdps_rank` · `cdps_score` · `attribution_score` · `gate_score` ·
`stability_score` · `invariance_score` · `perturbation_score` · `log2FC` ·
`DE_pvalue` · `DE_FDR` · `DE_direction` · `pathway_support_score` · `pathway_names` ·
`network_degree` · `network_centrality` · `clinical_support_score` ·
`strongest_clinical_variable` · `clinical_p_value` · `survival_p_value` ·
`hazard_direction` · `subgroup_robustness_score` · `external_concordance_rate` ·
`n_external_cohorts_tested` · `n_external_cohorts_concordant` ·
`final_priority_score` · `evidence_tier` · `missing_evidence_flags`

#### Interpretation

All genes are described as **computationally prioritized candidates** requiring
experimental confirmation. Tier 1 designation reflects convergent computational
support across multiple independent evidence streams — it does not imply
experimental validation or causal involvement in ESCA.

---

### Step 6b (Survival) — Survival Analysis & External Cohort Validation

**Purpose**: Performs Kaplan–Meier survival analysis for each of the top-25
CDPS-prioritised genes, generates TCGA tumour vs adjacent normal expression
boxplots, validates expression directionality in four independent GEO cohorts
(GSE53624, GSE53625, GSE161533, GSE38129), and produces a master evidence table.

All figures use **Times New Roman bold** typography and are output as SVG (primary)
and PDF. Both **individual** figures and **combined 5 × 5 publication panels** are
generated to meet Nature Communication submission standards.

**Module**: `cage.step6b_survival_external_validation`

#### Run Command

```bash
python -m cage.step6b_survival_external_validation \
  --expression-matrix outputs/step2_cohort/normalized_primary_matrix.csv \
  --metadata          outputs/step2_cohort/master_samples_primary.csv \
  --top25-ranking     outputs/step6b_top25_prioritization/tables/top25_final_priority_ranking.csv \
  --agilent-replication outputs/step8_agilent_validation/combined_de_replication.csv \
  --geo-replication   outputs/step8_geo_validation/combined_de_replication.csv \
  --geo-prepared-dir  outputs/step8_geo_prepared \
  --output-dir        outputs/step6b_survival_external
```

All inputs are optional — the module degrades gracefully when individual files
are absent.

#### Methods

**Survival**: TCGA-ESCA primary tumour samples (n=184) are dichotomised at the
per-gene median expression into high- and low-expression groups. Kaplan–Meier
curves are estimated with the product-limit method; statistical significance is
assessed by the log-rank (Mantel–Cox) test (pure NumPy, no external dependency).

**External validation**: Direction concordance between TCGA and each GEO cohort
is read from Step 8 pre-computed DE replication tables. For each dataset, raw
expression matrices are loaded to produce per-gene boxplots.

#### Outputs

```
outputs/step6b_survival_external/
├── figures/
│   ├── km/
│   │   ├── <gene>_KM_curve.svg         # individual Kaplan-Meier (× 22 genes with data)
│   │   └── combined_KM_all25.svg       # 5 × 5 combined panel (publication figure)
│   ├── boxplots/
│   │   ├── <gene>_TCGA_tumor_vs_normal.svg  # individual TCGA boxplot (× 25)
│   │   └── combined_TCGA_boxplots_all25.svg # 5 × 5 combined panel (publication figure)
│   ├── external/
│   │   ├── <GSE>_<gene>_boxplot.svg    # individual gene × dataset boxplot
│   │   └── <GSE>_all25_boxplots.svg    # per-dataset 5 × 5 panel (× 4 datasets)
│   ├── top25_external_concordance_heatmap.svg
│   └── top25_survival_summary_plot.svg
├── tables/
│   ├── top25_survival_summary.csv      # gene | median_cutoff | n_high | n_low | logrank_p | hazard_direction
│   ├── top25_external_validation.csv   # gene | dataset | effect | direction | concordant
│   └── top25_full_validation_summary.csv  # master table merging all evidence
├── reports/
│   ├── survival_methods.md
│   └── external_validation_summary.md
├── reproducibility.json
└── manifest.csv
```

#### Phase-Specific Options

| Flag | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `--expression-matrix` | Normalised expression matrix (samples × genes) |
| `--metadata` | Sample metadata with `vital_status`, `days_to_death`, `days_to_last_follow_up` |
| `--top25-ranking` | `top25_final_priority_ranking.csv` from Step 6b prioritization |
| `--agilent-replication` | `combined_de_replication.csv` from Step 8 Agilent validation |
| `--geo-replication` | `combined_de_replication.csv` from Step 8 GEO validation |
| `--geo-prepared-dir` | Root directory containing `<GSE>/processed/expression_gene_matrix.csv` |

