## GEO External Validation (Step 8 Subcommands)

CAGE integrates all GEO external validation under the Step 8 unified CLI.
The three sub-steps (download, Affymetrix validation, Agilent validation) are
accessible as subcommands of `step8_external_validation_and_release`:

```
python -m cage.step8_external_validation_and_release <subcommand> [options]
```

| Subcommand | Module | Purpose |
|------------|--------|---------|
| `prepare-geo` | `cage.step8_prepare_geo` | Download SOFT.gz + extract expression matrices |
| `validate-geo` | `cage.step8_geo_validation` | Affymetrix 4-cohort DE replication |
| `validate-agilent` | `cage.step8_agilent_validation` | Agilent GPL18109 validation |
| `release` | `cage.step8_runner` | Assemble release bundle |
| `all` | — | Run all four sub-steps in sequence |

> **Backward compatibility**: The old standalone scripts (`prepare_geo_external_validation.py`,
> `run_geo_external_validation.py`, `run_agilent_geo_validation.py`) now print a deprecation
> warning and delegate to the package modules. They continue to work but should not be used
> in new workflows.

### Validated Cohorts

| Accession | Platform | Tumor | Normal | Subcommand |
|-----------|----------|-------|--------|------------|
| GSE23400  | HG-U133A (Affymetrix) | 104 | 104 | `validate-geo` |
| GSE38129  | HG-U133A 2.0 (Affymetrix) | 30 | 30 | `validate-geo` |
| GSE161533 | HG-U133 Plus 2.0 (Affymetrix) | 56 | 28 | `validate-geo` |
| GSE20347  | HG-U133A 2.0 (Affymetrix) | 17 | 17 | `validate-geo` |
| GSE53624  | Agilent-038314 lncRNA+mRNA | 119 | 119 | `validate-agilent` |
| GSE53625  | Agilent-038314 lncRNA+mRNA | 179 | 179 | `validate-agilent` |

**Excluded** — GSE67269 (miRNA platform), GSE75241 (tumor-only).

---

### Step 8a — Download and Prepare GEO Datasets (`prepare-geo`)

Downloads SOFT.gz files from NCBI with automatic retry/resume, extracts probe
and gene expression matrices, infers tumor/normal labels from metadata, and maps
probes to gene symbols using platform annotation.

**Requirements**: run from the miniconda environment (needs `GEOparse`, `pandas`,
`requests`). Not available in the pipeline's pure-NumPy (PyMOL Python) environment.

```bash
python -m cage.step8_external_validation_and_release prepare-geo \
  --gse GSE53625 GSE53624 GSE23400 GSE38129 GSE161533 GSE20347 \
  --output-dir outputs/step8_geo_prepared \
  --max-retries 5 \
  --retry-delay 10 \
  --log-level INFO
```

**Key options**

| Flag | Default | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `--gse` | (required) | One or more GEO accessions to download |
| `--output-dir` | (required) | Root output directory |
| `--max-retries` | 5 | Download retry attempts per file |
| `--retry-delay` | 10.0 | Base seconds between retries (exponential back-off) |
| `--continue-on-error` | on | Skip failed accessions instead of aborting |
| `--log-level` | INFO | Logging verbosity (DEBUG for verbose) |

Downloads resume automatically via `Range: bytes=N-` headers.

**Outputs** (`outputs/step8_geo_prepared/<GSE>/`)

```
raw/<GSE>_family.soft.gz
processed/expression_gene_matrix.csv
metadata/sample_metadata_inferred.csv
external_validation_manifest.csv      # cross-dataset summary
```

---

### Step 8b — Affymetrix Validation (`validate-geo`)

Processes the four Affymetrix ESCC cohorts. Runs DE direction concordance and
optional classifier transfer in one pass.

**Requirements**: PyMOL Python / any Python 3.10+ with NumPy. The `cage`
package must be importable for `--run-model`.

```bash
python -m cage.step8_external_validation_and_release validate-geo \
  --geo-dir   outputs/step8_geo_prepared \
  --step5-dir outputs/step5_cdps \
  --step6-dir outputs/step6_validation \
  --step4-dir outputs/step4_deep_model \
  --output-dir outputs/step8_geo_validation \
  --top-k 100 \
  --run-model \
  --log-level INFO
```

**Key options**

| Flag | Default | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `--geo-dir` | (required) | Root GEO directory from `prepare-geo` |
| `--step5-dir` | (required) | Step 5 CDPS outputs (gene ranking) |
| `--step6-dir` | (required) | Step 6 outputs (reference DE directions) |
| `--step4-dir` | — | Step 4 outputs (checkpoints for `--run-model`) |
| `--output-dir` | (required) | Where to write all validation outputs |
| `--top-k` | 100 | Top K CDPS genes to test for DE concordance |
| `--run-model` | off | Run trained classifier on each cohort (AUROC) |
| `--skip` | — | Extra accessions to exclude |
| `--seed` | 2026 | RNG seed for ensemble model inference |

**Outputs** (`outputs/step8_geo_validation/`)

| File | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `per_dataset/<GSE>/de_replication.csv` | Gene-level concordance for that cohort |
| `per_dataset/<GSE>/model_metrics.json` | AUROC / sensitivity / specificity |
| `combined_de_replication.csv` | All cohorts stacked |
| `cross_cohort_concordance_summary.csv` | Per-gene concordance rate across cohorts |
| `cross_cohort_model_summary.csv` | Classifier metrics table |
| `geo_validation_summary.json` | Machine-readable run summary |
| `figures/` | B + C series figures (SVG) |

---

### Step 8c — Agilent Validation (`validate-agilent`)

Handles GSE53624 and GSE53625 (Agilent-038314 GPL18109). Because GPL18109
has no HGNC gene symbols, resolves probe-to-gene mapping via 60-mer exact
substring matching against NCBI RefSeq mRNAs (cached after first run).

**Requirements**: Python 3.10+ with NumPy (same as pipeline environment). NCBI
internet access required on the first run only.

```bash
python -m cage.step8_external_validation_and_release validate-agilent \
  --geo-dir   outputs/step8_geo_prepared \
  --step5-dir outputs/step5_cdps \
  --step6-dir outputs/step6_validation \
  --step4-dir outputs/step4_deep_model \
  --output-dir outputs/step8_agilent_validation \
  --datasets GSE53624 GSE53625 \
  --top-k 100 \
  --run-model \
  --log-level INFO
```

**Key options**

| Flag | Default | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `--geo-dir` | (required) | Root GEO directory from `prepare-geo` |
| `--step5-dir` | (required) | Step 5 CDPS outputs |
| `--step6-dir` | (required) | Step 6 reference DE directions |
| `--step4-dir` | — | Step 4 checkpoints for `--run-model` |
| `--output-dir` | (required) | Where to write outputs |
| `--datasets` | GSE53624 GSE53625 | Accessions to process |
| `--top-k` | 100 | Top K CDPS genes to test |
| `--run-model` | off | Run classifier on each cohort |
| `--collapse` | median | Probe-to-gene aggregation method |
| `--seed` | 2026 | RNG seed |

**Outputs** (`outputs/step8_agilent_validation/`)

| File | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `annotation/probe_gene_map.csv` | feature_id → gene_symbol (60-mer matched) |
| `annotation/annotation_summary.json` | Genes found / no probes / no RefSeq |
| `annotation/refseq_cache/` | Cached RefSeq FASTA per gene |
| `per_dataset/<GSE>/de_replication.csv` | Gene-level concordance table |
| `combined_de_replication.csv` | Both cohorts stacked |
| `concordance_summary.csv` | Per-gene concordance rate across both cohorts |
| `model_summary.csv` | AUROC / sensitivity / specificity table |
| `analysis_report.txt` | Human-readable narrative report |
| `validation_summary.json` | Machine-readable summary |
| `figures/` | A series figures (SVG) |

