### Step D — Generate Validation Figures (SVG)

`generate_validation_figures.py` reads all CSV/JSON outputs from Steps B and C and
produces 13 publication-quality SVG figures.  Requires any Python 3.10+ with
**matplotlib** and NumPy (e.g. the ChimeraX bundled Python, or a conda/venv
with matplotlib installed; **not** the pipeline's PyMOL Python).

```bash
python generate_validation_figures.py \
  --agilent-dir    outputs/agilent_validation \
  --affymetrix-dir outputs/geo_external_validation \
  --output-dir     outputs/figures \
  --verbose
```

**Options**

| Flag | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `--agilent-dir` | Root output dir from `run_agilent_geo_validation.py` |
| `--affymetrix-dir` | Root output dir from `run_geo_external_validation.py` |
| `--output-dir` | Where to write SVG figures (subdirs created automatically) |
| `--verbose` | Print path of each saved file |

**Outputs** (`outputs/figures/`)

| File | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `agilent/A1_direction_heatmap.svg` | Gene × cohort direction heatmap (Agilent 2 cohorts) |
| `agilent/A2_concordance_bar.svg` | Per-gene concordance rate bars — Agilent |
| `agilent/A3_probe_annotation_donut.svg` | Donut: genes with probes / no probe / no RefSeq NM_ |
| `agilent/A4_classifier_performance.svg` | AUROC / sensitivity / specificity — Agilent |
| `agilent/A5_effect_size_scatter.svg` | Effect size correlation GSE53624 vs GSE53625 |
| `agilent/A6_probes_per_gene.svg` | Number of 60-mer probes matched per gene |
| `affymetrix/B1_direction_heatmap.svg` | Gene × cohort direction heatmap (Affymetrix 4 cohorts) |
| `affymetrix/B2_concordance_bar.svg` | Per-gene concordance rate bars — Affymetrix |
| `affymetrix/B3_classifier_performance.svg` | AUROC / sensitivity / specificity — Affymetrix |
| `affymetrix/B4_concordance_distribution.svg` | Histogram + summary of concordance rate distribution |
| `combined/C1_all_cohorts_auroc.svg` | AUROC across all 6 cohorts, colour-coded by platform |
| `combined/C2_cross_platform_concordance_scatter.svg` | Per-gene Affymetrix rate vs Agilent rate |
| `combined/C3_combined_direction_heatmap.svg` | All 6 cohorts in one heatmap with platform separator |

**Colour scheme** (heatmaps): deep red = concordant UP, light salmon = discordant UP,
deep blue = concordant DOWN, light blue = discordant DOWN, grey = not testable,
white = gene not on platform.

---

### Validated Results Summary

Across **6 independent ESCC cohorts** (n = 980 samples):

| Metric | Affymetrix (4 cohorts) | Agilent (2 cohorts) |
|--------|----------------------|---------------------|
| Samples | 384 (195T / 189N) | 596 (298T / 298N) |
| Genes testable | 60–87 / 100 | 89 / 100 |
| DE concordance (overall) | 76–82% | 75–76% |
| Genes 100% concordant across all cohorts | 56 | 67 |
| Classifier AUROC range | 0.39–0.62 | 0.49–0.58 |

Genes concordant across **all** tested cohorts on both platforms include:
`MMP9`, `BGN`, `COL1A1`, `TP63`, `KRT16`, `KRT17`, `MAGEA3`, `CXCL13`,
`FAP`, `LGALS4`, `ABCA8`, `MLF1`, `ATP8A1`, `PRRX2`, `FCGR3A`, `NXPH4`,
`GMDS`, `IFI44L`, `SIX1`, `CLDN10`, `PSCA`, `PTGES`, `AEBP1`, `FAP`,
`LPIN2`, `CYP24A1`, `HMGN5`, `DNALI1`, `RIMS2`, `GCKR`.

> **Note on classifier domain shift**: The model is trained on TCGA RNA-seq
> (DESeq2 VST) and applied to microarray log-intensity after per-gene
> z-scoring.  AUROC values reflect cross-platform generalisability rather
> than held-out TCGA performance; results should be interpreted as domain
> transfer benchmarks.

