## Global CLI Options

All pipeline steps share a unified set of global options:

| Flag | Default | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `--input-dir` | (required*) | Directory containing inputs for this step |
| `--output-dir` | (required) | Directory for outputs (tables, figures, logs) |
| `--seed` | 2026 | Random seed for full reproducibility |
| `--n-threads` | ½ CPU count | Worker threads for parallelisable operations |
| `--overwrite` | off | Regenerate outputs even if they already exist |
| `--log-level` | INFO | Logging verbosity (`DEBUG`, `INFO`, `WARNING`, `ERROR`) |
| `--version` | — | Print CAGE version and exit |

*Steps 5–8 accept per-phase `--stepN-dir` flags instead of `--input-dir`.

---

## Figure and Visualization Standards

All figures produced by CAGE adhere to 2026 publication-grade
standards suitable for Nature Communications and equivalent journals:

| Property | Standard |
|----------|----------|
| **Primary format** | SVG |
| **Additional formats** | PDF, PNG (via `--extra-figure-format`) |
| **Typography** | Bold Roman/serif only (Times New Roman → Times → STIXGeneral → DejaVu Serif) |
| **Colour palette** | Nature manuscript-style (10 categorical + 12 semantic colours) |
| **Accessibility** | Colorblind-friendly where feasible |
| **Design** | Clean, minimal; no chart junk; balanced whitespace |
| **Rasterisation** | High-DPI for PDF/PNG exports |
| **Configuration** | `--font-family`, `--font-size`, `--palette`, `--figure-format` |

#### Figure CLI Options

| Flag | Default | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `--figure-format` | svg | Primary output format |
| `--extra-figure-format` | — | Additional formats (repeatable: `--extra-figure-format pdf --extra-figure-format png`) |
| `--font-family` | Times New Roman | Preferred serif font |
| `--font-size` | 10 | Base font size in points |
| `--palette` | nature | Colour palette |

All styling is centralised in `cage/publication_style.py`, ensuring
consistency across all pipeline phases.

